P\{(j,m)\cap(j,m+1)\cap(i,n)\} =  P\{(j,m)\}P\{(j-j,m+1-m)\}P\{(i-j,n-(m+1))\} 
= P\{(j,m)\}P\{(0,1)\}P\{(i-j,n-m-1)\}  
= {m \choose j} p^j (1-p)^{m-j} {1 \choose 0} p^0 (1-p)^1  {n-m-1 \choose i-j} p^{i-j} (1-p)^{n-m-1-i+j}  
= {m \choose j}  {n-m-1 \choose i-j} p^{i} (1-p)^{n} 
